'''Aspilogia''' is a word that means [[armory (heraldry)|armory]] or [[heraldry]].  It was coined by Sir [[Henry Spelman]] ([[1564]]-[[1641]]) as the title to his [[Latin]] [[treatise]] on [[Coat of Arms|coats of arms]].  The ''Dictionary of National Biography'' and the ''Revised Medieval Latin Word List'' assign the appearance of the word to about [[1595]], perhaps earlier.  Sir [[Anthony Richard Wagner|Anthony Wagner]] argues in his ''A Catalogue of Medieval Arms'' ([[1950]]) that on [[etymology|etymological]] grounds a better form of the word would have been "Aspidologia," but retains Spelman's [[innovation]] on the basis of long [[tradition]].

